@page "/about"
<PageTitle>About Me</PageTitle>
<style>
    .warning-list-item {
        color: #FAF0E6 !important;
    }
</style>


<MudContainer Class="mt-16">
    <MudText Align="Align.Center" Typo="Typo.h1" Color="Color.Warning">About Me</MudText>
    <MudContainer Class="mt-16">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Color="Color.Warning">
            I'm a HUGE gamer! Ever since I was a kid, I've been hooked on the immersive worlds and challenging gameplay of video games. World of Warcraft grabbed me early – started playing it at eight, sharing an account with my mom. Walking through Ashenvale as a Night Elf priest felt like pure magic.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Color="Color.Warning">
            Warcraft 3, thanks to my uncle, blew my mind with its level editor. That's when I thought, "I wanna be a game developer!" Minecraft days with my cousin were a blast – building automated machines and diving into Java for my first modding attempts.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Color="Color.Warning">
            That led my 12 year old self to copy a YouTube tutorial, in which I 'made' my first game, and then jumped into Unity and C#. Playing games with family deepened our connections. Whether teaming up with my dad in WoW or crafting structures with my cousin in Minecraft, those moments fueled my passion for game development.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Color="Color.Warning">
            Here are some of my gaming achievements:
        </MudText>

        <MudList Dense>
            <MudListItem>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Warning">
                    <strong>World of Warcraft:</strong>
                </MudText>
                <MudList>
                    <MudListItem class="warning-list-item">Top 10% M+ rating in Dragonflight S2.</MudListItem>
                    <MudListItem class="warning-list-item">Keystone Master for SL S3/S4 and DF S1.</MudListItem>
                    <MudListItem class="warning-list-item">AoTC for Legion, BFA, stopped halfway into SL. All with my family!</MudListItem>
                </MudList>
            </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Warning">
                    <strong>Destiny 2:</strong>
                </MudText>
                <MudList>
                    <MudListItem class="warning-list-item">Cleared raids with friends, flawless in Trials of Osiris, completed dungeons and raids on release.</MudListItem>
                </MudList>
            </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Warning">
                    <strong>Overwatch 1 & 2:</strong>
                </MudText>
                <MudList>
                    <MudListItem class="warning-list-item">Reached Platinum with a full 5/6 stack.</MudListItem>
                </MudList>
            </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Warning">
                    <strong>Diablo 3:</strong>
                </MudText>
                <MudList>
                    <MudListItem class="warning-list-item">Held a top 100 rank for a Challenge Rift.</MudListItem>
                </MudList>
            </MudListItem>
        </MudList>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Color="Color.Warning">
            My favorite games include WoW, Diablo, Risk of Rain, Minecraft, Baldur's Gate 3, Destiny, and Overwatch.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Color="Color.Warning">
            And when I'm not gaming, I'm into some awesome books like Dune, Red Rising Series (seriously, a must-read!), Harry Potter, Project Hail Mary, The Martian, Bobiverse Series, and Ready Player One.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Color="Color.Warning">
            Here's to many more epic gaming adventures! 🎮✨
        </MudText>
    </MudContainer>
    
</MudContainer>

@code {
    [CascadingParameter] protected MudTheme Theme { get; set; }
}
